<dl id="n06154l"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06154l">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06154l"> 154(l)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> apostolic days <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n06154l"><li>FW 62.13 </li><li><a href="../../flex/c/lexc.htm#n06154l">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/c/l39c.htm#n06154l">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n06154l">MS BL 47471b-10v</ms> </li><li>JJA 45:151 <a name="c20d" href="../../ff/fdra/cda.htm#c20d">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/c/c20d.htm#n06154l">Draft: I.3&sect;2.0</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[from the Ninth Article of the Creed]</font> &ldquo;COMMUNION.&rdquo;&mdash;Fellowship, united in one family, bound together by mutual affections, companionship, and sympathy. Our blessed Lord prays for this union &ldquo;that they may be one;&rdquo; this holy bond was strikingly manifested in <mark>Apostolic days</mark>: they &ldquo;were of one heart and of one soul.&rdquo; <small> Anonymous, <a name="ATCC" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ATCC"><cite title="source">Analysis of the Church Catechism</cite></a> (1879) 25</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
